@Dusk

Hi,

I'm selling the 2014 special edition (180ml) on Ebay and I'm based in Germany. Let me know if you're interested.

@bc92
Sad to read, that a fragrance where you pay your hard earned money for, not stays a decent couple of years with the same smell and quality, and also with good storage it goes BAD!

Looks that expensive fragrances, not deliver always quality for the price!

@ts01
C.L.U.B. Is a lot different from Club. I prefer Club, and find the new version to be a more modern and youthful reform of the original while not strictly adhering to the dna of the original (albeit I do catch whispers of the og in there somewhere)
Luckily the OG is still on shelves in certain stores. I would say grab it while you can.

@ts01 the Club is nice. Minty, fresh, and a bit classic/old school. I am enjoying it at the moment and while I find it to be somewhat one dimensional compared to others in the ADP line (including its replacement C.L.U.B., which is significantly brighter/more modern), I’m nonetheless really enjoying it’s herbal and very natural green vibe… it’s like a sophisticated and very un-synthetic take on Brut (which I’d love to find a niche version of) in some passing regard.
Regarding Futura, I’m not sure why both myself and the sales associate got the pickles note… it’s seems perhaps that the sage may have been a bit concentrated in the direct blast to the back of my hand that I used to test it., or else the wood note somehow soured (?).. I really dug the liveliness of it, but the pickles vibe was legit and undeniable to us. I get how that assessment may offend some, but that was the impression we got at the time…Will try it again soon to see if the impression persist, otherwise I’ll acquire Essenza or Cipresso at some point this week as they both tested rather nicely for me. Just wished ADP as a whole had stronger lasting power.

Edit: retested the Futura… and it wore much nicer this time. I’ts quite green which is exactly what I want.

@perfume4everyone,
To evaluate the quality of a perfume’s essence and its ingredients, we start by testing on neutral materials like paper. You don’t test on human skin for long periods because contrary to what you seem to do normal people shower once or twice a day. In that way you lost essence longevity.
You, however, sound like you live in a cave without running water, which is why you’re desperate for perfume to smother your stench. ps: if you won’t bathe, not even a $10,000 bottle will help.

@Dark-X Then is a good thing that I'm +40 because I love it! If one has to be that age to properly wear this perfume, then I would say that's one of the pro's of turning 40.

I agree, this feels like a leather perfume, and it's a very nice one. I also agree is a luxurious scent and that it is for more mature men. I only wish it had better performance, perhaps the new eau de parfum version will be an improvement in that area.

Why didn't I buy it the day I bought Sandalo and Leather at a discount? Answer: Because I'm an idiot; that, and because my wife was next to me.
